.Dd April 19, 2026
.Dt PROWL-UNIT 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm prowl-unit
.Nd prowld job configuration format
.Sh DESCRIPTION
A unit file is a declarative configuration file that defines a job managed by
.Xr prowld 8 .
Jobs can be long-running daemons, oneshot tasks, schedule-driven timers,
or on-demand services triggered by socket activity.
.Pp
Unit files are parsed by
.Xr libucl 3
and support UCL, JSON, and simplified YAML-like syntax.
Files must have the
.Pa .unit
extension and be located in one of the search directories described in
.Xr prowld 8 .
.Sh SCHEMA
The following fields are recognised at the top level of a unit file:
.Ss Identity
.Bl -tag -width "description"
.It Va label
.Pq required, string
Unique reverse-DNS identifier for the job,
e.g.,
.Dq org.midnightbsd.sshd .
Used for dependency resolution and management via
.Xr prowlctl 8 .
.It Va description
.Pq string
Human-readable description of the service.
.It Va type
.Pq string
One of:
.Bl -tag -width "oneshot" -compact
.It Cm daemon
A long-running process (default).
.It Cm oneshot
A task that runs once and is considered complete on successful exit.
.It Cm timer
A job activated by a schedule or interval.
.It Cm socket
A job activated by incoming socket connections.
.El
.It Va rc_name
.Pq string
The prefix used for the
.Va _enable
variable in
.Pa /etc/rc.conf .
Defaults to the last component of
.Va label .
.El
.Ss Execution
.Bl -tag -width "working_directory"
.It Va program
.Pq string
Absolute path to the executable.
Required unless
.Va arguments[0]
is an absolute path.
.It Va arguments
.Pq array of strings
Argument vector passed to the process.
The executable name is automatically prepended as
.Vt argv[0] .
.It Va environment
.Pq object
Key/value pairs set in the child's environment.
The process does not inherit the environment of
.Xr prowld 8 .
.It Va working_directory
.Pq string
Directory to
.Xr chdir 2
into before execution.
.It Va root_directory
.Pq string
Directory to
.Xr chroot 2
into.
Requires
.Va user
to be set for security.
.It Va user , Va group
.Pq string
User and group names to drop privileges to.
.It Va umask
.Pq string
Octal umask (e.g.,
.Dq 0022 ) .
.El
.Ss Lifecycle
.Bl -tag -width "throttle_interval"
.It Va run_at_load
.Pq boolean
If true, start the job automatically when loaded.
.It Va keep_alive
.Pq boolean or object
Restart policy.
See
.Xr prowld 8
for detailed object keys:
.Va always ,
.Va crashed ,
.Va successful_exit .
.It Va throttle_interval
.Pq integer
Minimum seconds between restart attempts.
Default: 10.
.It Va exit_timeout
.Pq integer
Seconds to wait after
.Dv SIGTERM
before sending
.Dv SIGKILL .
Default: 20.
.It Va shutdown_wait
.Pq boolean
Wait for clean exit during system shutdown.
.El
.Ss Dependencies
.Bl -tag -width "requires"
.It Va requires
.Pq array of strings
Capability names that must be running for this job to start.
.It Va wants
.Pq array of strings
Like
.Va requires
but failure of the dependency is non-fatal.
.It Va provides
.Pq array of strings
Capabilities this job satisfies (e.g.,
.Dq network ) .
.It Va before , Va after
.Pq array of strings
Explicit ordering constraints against other job labels.
.El
.Ss Scheduling (Timers)
The
.Va schedule
field is an object used by
.Cm type :
.Cm timer
jobs:
.Bl -tag -width "on_boot_delay"
.It Va interval
.Pq integer
Recurring interval in seconds.
.It Va on_boot_delay
.Pq integer
One-shot delay after the daemon starts.
.It Va calendar
.Pq object
Cron-like triggers.
Fields:
.Va minute
(0-59),
.Va hour
(0-23),
.Va day
(1-31),
.Va month
(1-12),
.Va weekday
(0-6, Sunday is 0).
Fields support integers or the
.Dq *
wildcard.
.El
.Ss Socket Activation
The
.Va sockets
field is an object mapping logical names to socket descriptions.
Keys in each description:
.Va type
(stream, dgram, seqpacket),
.Va family
(inet, inet6, unix),
.Va path
(AF_UNIX only),
.Va port
(inet only),
.Va host
(bind address),
.Va backlog .
.Sh EXAMPLES
A simple periodic cleanup task:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
  "label": "org.midnightbsd.cleanup",
  "type": "timer",
  "program": "/usr/libexec/mycleanup",
  "schedule": {
    "interval": 3600
  }
}
.Ed
.Pp
A daemon with dependencies and socket activation:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
  "label": "org.midnightbsd.myservice",
  "description": "My Network Service",
  "program": "/usr/local/bin/mysrv",
  "requires": ["network"],
  "sockets": {
    "http": { "port": 80, "family": "inet" }
  }
}
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr libucl 3 ,
.Xr prowld 8 ,
.Xr prowlctl 8 ,
.Xr prowl-generator 8
.Sh HISTORY
.Nm
first appeared in MidnightBSD 4.1.
